 Zimbabwe has experienced its first coronavirus death. Journalist Zororo Makamba has become Zimbabwe's first victim of the dealy virus. According to ZBC News, Health and Child Care Minister Obediah Moyo confirmed the death of a30-year-old Makamba. Makamba was the second person to test positive for the virus in the Southern African country. Zimbabwean businessman Mutumwa Mawere confirmed the passing via his social media.  He tweeted: Mr Zororo Makamba, the son of Mr James Makamba has passed on. MHSRIEP. I have just learned of this tragic loss of life due to the virus. A giant with so much potential has fallen. Corona is real. Let us pause and reflect. Life is too precious. Zororo was the son of Zimbabwean businessman James Makamba.  Tributes poured in for Makamba. Zimbabwean politician Jonathan Moyo said it was a "tragedy". "Words alone cannot capture and convey the profound pain from this unfathomable tragedy. Heartfelt condolences to the Makamba family! #RIPZororoMakamba."       